threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, MIPS, MIPS-I version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, no section header

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This sample is a MIPS-based IoT botnet agent, likely a variant of Mirai or Gafgyt. It exhibits classic malware behaviors including self-daemonization (via setsid and redirecting descriptors to /dev/null), a 'killer' module designed to terminate competing malware processes (seen in sub_407588), and a sophisticated DDoS engine. Specifically, sub_4002d0 implements a Layer 7 HTTP flood capable of handling cookies, following redirects, and attempting to bypass anti-DDoS protections such as Cloudflare and DOSarrest. Multiple other functions (e.g., sub_4034e0, sub_4047a8) implement various Layer 4 network flooding attacks. The binary contains a hardcoded C2 IP address 31.56.120.29.
